data-testid="jobsearch-JobInfoHeader-companyLocation"><span>Boston, MA</span></div></div></div><div aria-orientation="horizontal" class="css-92hmla e15p7aqh1" role="separator"><span class="css-1b6omqv esbq1260"><span>&amp;nbsp;</span></span></div></div><div class="css-eynugf eu4oa1w0" data-testid="benefits-test" id="benefits"><h2 class="css-gfuqm7 e1tiznh50" id="benefitsSectionTitle">Benefits<div class="css-1opnqdm e1wnkr790">Pulled from the full job description</div></h2><div class="css-1oelwk6 eu4oa1w0"><div class="css-k3ey05 eu4oa1w0"><span class="css-c62ar3 e1wnkr790"><ul class="css-8tnble eu4oa1w0"><li class="css-kyg8or eu4oa1w0">Work from home</li></ul></span></div></div><div aria-orientation="horizontal" class="css-vms2hq e15p7aqh1" role="separator"><span class="css-1b6omqv esbq1260"><span>&amp;nbsp;</span></span></div></div><div id="jobDescriptionTitle"><h2 class="css-wpzt8u e1tiznh50" id="jobDescriptionTitleHeading" tabindex="-1">Full job description</h2></div><div class="jobsearch-JobComponent-description css-16y4thd eu4oa1w0" id="jobDescriptionText"><p></p>
<div>
 <p>IMP is currently seeking candidates for a paid internship starting in December 2024. The ideal candidate will have an active interest in investment management, compliance, and business analysis. As an intern, you will be responsible for learning IMP’s proprietary CLEAR Compliance® system, assisting with project tracking, writing and testing basic compliance rules, and assisting other employees with general project tasks. Interns will be exposed to and/or receive training in a variety of areas, including investment compliance, vendor systems, financial securities, Agile project management, business analysis, and SQL.</p>
 <p><b>Duration</b></p>
 <p>For current 4th year students, the internship will be throughout the school year as class schedules allow. Exceptional hires may be offered a full-time position with the company at the end of the internship.</p>
 <p><b>Eligible Applicants</b></p>
 <p>The following candidates are encouraged to apply:</p>
 <ul>
  <li>Currently enrolled 4th year students in pursuit of a Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Business, Economics, Accounting, or a related field</li>
  <li>Honorably discharged military veterans</li>
 </ul>
 <p><b>Requirements</b></p>
 <ul>
  <li>Interest in investment management, compliance, and business analysis</li>
  <li>Solid written and oral communication skills</li>
  <li>Familiarity with Microsoft Office products, especially Excel and PowerPoint</li>
  <li>Knowledge of SQL and relational databases is a plus</li>
  <li>Must be able to pass an IMP-administered logic test</li>
  <li>Must be authorized to work in the United States</li>
  <li>Must be able to work during normal business hours on a set weekly schedule</li>
  <li>Being able to commute to our Boston office is a plus</li>
  <li>Ability to work from home - Hybrid</li>
 </ul>
 <p>Salary: $30/hr<br/> Hours: Minimum of 10-15 hours per week is required<br/> <br/> Location: Boston, MA/Hybrid</p>
</div>

id="benefitsSectionTitle">Benefits<div class="css-1opnqdm e1wnkr790">Pulled from the full job description</div></h2><div class="css-1oelwk6 eu4oa1w0"><div class="css-k3ey05 eu4oa1w0"><span class="css-c62ar3 e1wnkr790"><ul class="css-8tnble eu4oa1w0"><li class="css-kyg8or eu4oa1w0">Work from home</li></ul></span></div></div><div aria-orientation="horizontal" class="css-vms2hq e15p7aqh1" role="separator"><span class="css-1b6omqv esbq1260"><span>&amp;nbsp;</span></span></div></div><div id="jobDescriptionTitle"><h2 class="css-wpzt8u e1tiznh50" id="jobDescriptionTitleHeading" tabindex="-1">Full job description</h2></div><div class="jobsearch-JobComponent-description css-16y4thd eu4oa1w0" id="jobDescriptionText"><p></p>
<div>
 <p>IMP is currently seeking candidates for a paid internship starting in December 2024. The ideal candidate will have an active interest in investment management, compliance, and business analysis. As an intern, you will be responsible for learning IMP’s proprietary CLEAR Compliance® system, assisting with project tracking, writing and testing basic compliance rules, and assisting other employees with general project tasks. Interns will be exposed to and/or receive training in a variety of areas, including investment compliance, vendor systems, financial securities, Agile project management, business analysis, and SQL.</p>
 <p><b>Duration</b></p>
 <p>For current 4th year students, the internship will be throughout the school year as class schedules allow. Exceptional hires may be offered a full-time position with the company at the end of the internship.</p>
 <p><b>Eligible Applicants</b></p>
 <p>The following candidates are encouraged to apply:</p>
 <ul>
  <li>Currently enrolled 4th year students in pursuit of a Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Business, Economics, Accounting, or a related field</li>
  <li>Honorably discharged military veterans</li>
 </ul>
 <p><b>Requirements</b></p>
 <ul>
  <li>Interest in investment management, compliance, and business analysis</li>
  <li>Solid written and oral communication skills</li>
  <li>Familiarity with Microsoft Office products, especially Excel and PowerPoint</li>
  <li>Knowledge of SQL and relational databases is a plus</li>
  <li>Must be able to pass an IMP-administered logic test</li>
  <li>Must be authorized to work in the United States</li>
  <li>Must be able to work during normal business hours on a set weekly schedule</li>
  <li>Being able to commute to our Boston office is a plus</li>
  <li>Ability to work from home - Hybrid</li>
 </ul>
 <p>Salary: $30/hr<br/> Hours: Minimum of 10-15 hours per week is required<br/> <br/> Location: Boston, MA/Hybrid</p>
</div>

data-testid="jobsearch-JobInfoHeader-companyLocation"><span>Boston, MA</span></div></div></div><div aria-orientation="horizontal" class="css-92hmla e15p7aqh1" role="separator"><span class="css-1b6omqv esbq1260"><span>&amp;nbsp;</span></span></div></div><div class="css-eynugf eu4oa1w0" data-testid="benefits-test" id="benefits"><h2 class="css-gfuqm7 e1tiznh50" id="benefitsSectionTitle">Benefits<div class="css-1opnqdm e1wnkr790">Pulled from the full job description</div></h2><div class="css-1oelwk6 eu4oa1w0"><div class="css-k3ey05 eu4oa1w0"><span class="css-c62ar3 e1wnkr790"><ul class="css-8tnble eu4oa1w0"><li class="css-kyg8or eu4oa1w0">Work from home</li></ul></span></div></div><div aria-orientation="horizontal" class="css-vms2hq e15p7aqh1" role="separator"><span class="css-1b6omqv esbq1260"><span>&amp;nbsp;</span></span></div></div><div id="jobDescriptionTitle"><h2 class="css-wpzt8u e1tiznh50" id="jobDescriptionTitleHeading" tabindex="-1">Full job description</h2></div><div class="jobsearch-JobComponent-description css-16y4thd eu4oa1w0" id="jobDescriptionText"><p></p>
<div>
 <p>IMP is currently seeking candidates for a paid internship starting in December 2024. The ideal candidate will have an active interest in investment management, compliance, and business analysis. As an intern, you will be responsible for learning IMP’s proprietary CLEAR Compliance® system, assisting with project tracking, writing and testing basic compliance rules, and assisting other employees with general project tasks. Interns will be exposed to and/or receive training in a variety of areas, including investment compliance, vendor systems, financial securities, Agile project management, business analysis, and SQL.</p>
 <p><b>Duration</b></p>
 <p>For current 4th year students, the internship will be throughout the school year as class schedules allow. Exceptional hires may be offered a full-time position with the company at the end of the internship.</p>
 <p><b>Eligible Applicants</b></p>
 <p>The following candidates are encouraged to apply:</p>
 <ul>
  <li>Currently enrolled 4th year students in pursuit of a Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Business, Economics, Accounting, or a related field</li>
  <li>Honorably discharged military veterans</li>
 </ul>
 <p><b>Requirements</b></p>
 <ul>
  <li>Interest in investment management, compliance, and business analysis</li>
  <li>Solid written and oral communication skills</li>
  <li>Familiarity with Microsoft Office products, especially Excel and PowerPoint</li>
  <li>Knowledge of SQL and relational databases is a plus</li>
  <li>Must be able to pass an IMP-administered logic test</li>
  <li>Must be authorized to work in the United States</li>
  <li>Must be able to work during normal business hours on a set weekly schedule</li>
  <li>Being able to commute to our Boston office is a plus</li>
  <li>Ability to work from home - Hybrid</li>
 </ul>
 <p>Salary: $30/hr<br/> Hours: Minimum of 10-15 hours per week is required<br/> <br/> Location: Boston, MA/Hybrid</p>
</div>

role="separator"><span class="css-1b6omqv esbq1260"><span>&amp;nbsp;</span></span></div></div><div id="jobDescriptionTitle"><h2 class="css-wpzt8u e1tiznh50" id="jobDescriptionTitleHeading" tabindex="-1">Full job description</h2></div><div class="jobsearch-JobComponent-description css-16y4thd eu4oa1w0" id="jobDescriptionText"><p></p>
<div>
 <p>IMP is currently seeking candidates for a paid internship starting in December 2024. The ideal candidate will have an active interest in investment management, compliance, and business analysis. As an intern, you will be responsible for learning IMP’s proprietary CLEAR Compliance® system, assisting with project tracking, writing and testing basic compliance rules, and assisting other employees with general project tasks. Interns will be exposed to and/or receive training in a variety of areas, including investment compliance, vendor systems, financial securities, Agile project management, business analysis, and SQL.</p>
 <p><b>Duration</b></p>
 <p>For current 4th year students, the internship will be throughout the school year as class schedules allow. Exceptional hires may be offered a full-time position with the company at the end of the internship.</p>
 <p><b>Eligible Applicants</b></p>
 <p>The following candidates are encouraged to apply:</p>
 <ul>
  <li>Currently enrolled 4th year students in pursuit of a Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Business, Economics, Accounting, or a related field</li>
  <li>Honorably discharged military veterans</li>
 </ul>
 <p><b>Requirements</b></p>
 <ul>
  <li>Interest in investment management, compliance, and business analysis</li>
  <li>Solid written and oral communication skills</li>
  <li>Familiarity with Microsoft Office products, especially Excel and PowerPoint</li>
  <li>Knowledge of SQL and relational databases is a plus</li>
  <li>Must be able to pass an IMP-administered logic test</li>
  <li>Must be authorized to work in the United States</li>
  <li>Must be able to work during normal business hours on a set weekly schedule</li>
  <li>Being able to commute to our Boston office is a plus</li>
  <li>Ability to work from home - Hybrid</li>
 </ul>
 <p>Salary: $30/hr<br/> Hours: Minimum of 10-15 hours per week is required<br/> <br/> Location: Boston, MA/Hybrid</p>
</div>

data-testid="jobsearch-JobInfoHeader-companyLocation"><span>Boston, MA</span></div></div></div><div aria-orientation="horizontal" class="css-92hmla e15p7aqh1" role="separator"><span class="css-1b6omqv esbq1260"><span>&amp;nbsp;</span></span></div></div><div class="css-eynugf eu4oa1w0" data-testid="benefits-test" id="benefits"><h2 class="css-gfuqm7 e1tiznh50" id="benefitsSectionTitle">Benefits<div class="css-1opnqdm e1wnkr790">Pulled from the full job description</div></h2><div class="css-1oelwk6 eu4oa1w0"><div class="css-k3ey05 eu4oa1w0"><span class="css-c62ar3 e1wnkr790"><ul class="css-8tnble eu4oa1w0"><li class="css-kyg8or eu4oa1w0">Work from home</li></ul></span></div></div><div aria-orientation="horizontal" class="css-vms2hq e15p7aqh1" role="separator"><span class="css-1b6omqv esbq1260"><span>&amp;nbsp;</span></span></div></div><div id="jobDescriptionTitle"><h2 class="css-wpzt8u e1tiznh50" id="jobDescriptionTitleHeading" tabindex="-1">Full job description</h2></div><div class="jobsearch-JobComponent-description css-16y4thd eu4oa1w0" id="jobDescriptionText"><p></p>
<div>
 <p>IMP is currently seeking candidates for a paid internship starting in December 2024. The ideal candidate will have an active interest in investment management, compliance, and business analysis. As an intern, you will be responsible for learning IMP’s proprietary CLEAR Compliance® system, assisting with project tracking, writing and testing basic compliance rules, and assisting other employees with general project tasks. Interns will be exposed to and/or receive training in a variety of areas, including investment compliance, vendor systems, financial securities, Agile project management, business analysis, and SQL.</p>
 <p><b>Duration</b></p>
 <p>For current 4th year students, the internship will be throughout the school year as class schedules allow. Exceptional hires may be offered a full-time position with the company at the end of the internship.</p>
 <p><b>Eligible Applicants</b></p>
 <p>The following candidates are encouraged to apply:</p>
 <ul>
  <li>Currently enrolled 4th year students in pursuit of a Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Business, Economics, Accounting, or a related field</li>
  <li>Honorably discharged military veterans</li>
 </ul>
 <p><b>Requirements</b></p>
 <ul>
  <li>Interest in investment management, compliance, and business analysis</li>
  <li>Solid written and oral communication skills</li>
  <li>Familiarity with Microsoft Office products, especially Excel and PowerPoint</li>
  <li>Knowledge of SQL and relational databases is a plus</li>
  <li>Must be able to pass an IMP-administered logic test</li>
  <li>Must be authorized to work in the United States</li>
  <li>Must be able to work during normal business hours on a set weekly schedule</li>
  <li>Being able to commute to our Boston office is a plus</li>
  <li>Ability to work from home - Hybrid</li>
 </ul>
 <p>Salary: $30/hr<br/> Hours: Minimum of 10-15 hours per week is required<br/> <br/> Location: Boston, MA/Hybrid</p>
</div>

esbq1260"><span>&amp;nbsp;</span></span></div></div><div class="css-eynugf eu4oa1w0" data-testid="benefits-test" id="benefits"><h2 class="css-gfuqm7 e1tiznh50" id="benefitsSectionTitle">Benefits<div class="css-1opnqdm e1wnkr790">Pulled from the full job description</div></h2><div class="css-1oelwk6 eu4oa1w0"><div class="css-k3ey05 eu4oa1w0"><span class="css-c62ar3 e1wnkr790"><ul class="css-8tnble eu4oa1w0"><li class="css-kyg8or eu4oa1w0">Work from home</li></ul></span></div></div><div aria-orientation="horizontal" class="css-vms2hq e15p7aqh1" role="separator"><span class="css-1b6omqv esbq1260"><span>&amp;nbsp;</span></span></div></div><div id="jobDescriptionTitle"><h2 class="css-wpzt8u e1tiznh50" id="jobDescriptionTitleHeading" tabindex="-1">Full job description</h2></div><div class="jobsearch-JobComponent-description css-16y4thd eu4oa1w0" id="jobDescriptionText"><p></p>
<div>
 <p>IMP is currently seeking candidates for a paid internship starting in December 2024. The ideal candidate will have an active interest in investment management, compliance, and business analysis. As an intern, you will be responsible for learning IMP’s proprietary CLEAR Compliance® system, assisting with project tracking, writing and testing basic compliance rules, and assisting other employees with general project tasks. Interns will be exposed to and/or receive training in a variety of areas, including investment compliance, vendor systems, financial securities, Agile project management, business analysis, and SQL.</p>
 <p><b>Duration</b></p>
 <p>For current 4th year students, the internship will be throughout the school year as class schedules allow. Exceptional hires may be offered a full-time position with the company at the end of the internship.</p>
 <p><b>Eligible Applicants</b></p>
 <p>The following candidates are encouraged to apply:</p>
 <ul>
  <li>Currently enrolled 4th year students in pursuit of a Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Business, Economics, Accounting, or a related field</li>
  <li>Honorably discharged military veterans</li>
 </ul>
 <p><b>Requirements</b></p>
 <ul>
  <li>Interest in investment management, compliance, and business analysis</li>
  <li>Solid written and oral communication skills</li>
  <li>Familiarity with Microsoft Office products, especially Excel and PowerPoint</li>
  <li>Knowledge of SQL and relational databases is a plus</li>
  <li>Must be able to pass an IMP-administered logic test</li>
  <li>Must be authorized to work in the United States</li>
  <li>Must be able to work during normal business hours on a set weekly schedule</li>
  <li>Being able to commute to our Boston office is a plus</li>
  <li>Ability to work from home - Hybrid</li>
 </ul>
 <p>Salary: $30/hr<br/> Hours: Minimum of 10-15 hours per week is required<br/> <br/> Location: Boston, MA/Hybrid</p>
</div>

data-testid="jobsearch-JobInfoHeader-companyLocation"><span>Boston, MA</span></div></div></div><div aria-orientation="horizontal" class="css-92hmla e15p7aqh1" role="separator"><span class="css-1b6omqv esbq1260"><span>&amp;nbsp;</span></span></div></div><div class="css-eynugf eu4oa1w0" data-testid="benefits-test" id="benefits"><h2 class="css-gfuqm7 e1tiznh50" id="benefitsSectionTitle">Benefits<div class="css-1opnqdm e1wnkr790">Pulled from the full job description</div></h2><div class="css-1oelwk6 eu4oa1w0"><div class="css-k3ey05 eu4oa1w0"><span class="css-c62ar3 e1wnkr790"><ul class="css-8tnble eu4oa1w0"><li class="css-kyg8or eu4oa1w0">Work from home</li></ul></span></div></div><div aria-orientation="horizontal" class="css-vms2hq e15p7aqh1" role="separator"><span class="css-1b6omqv esbq1260"><span>&amp;nbsp;</span></span></div></div><div id="jobDescriptionTitle"><h2 class="css-wpzt8u e1tiznh50" id="jobDescriptionTitleHeading" tabindex="-1">Full job description</h2></div><div class="jobsearch-JobComponent-description css-16y4thd eu4oa1w0" id="jobDescriptionText"><p></p>
<div>
 <p>IMP is currently seeking candidates for a paid internship starting in December 2024. The ideal candidate will have an active interest in investment management, compliance, and business analysis. As an intern, you will be responsible for learning IMP’s proprietary CLEAR Compliance® system, assisting with project tracking, writing and testing basic compliance rules, and assisting other employees with general project tasks. Interns will be exposed to and/or receive training in a variety of areas, including investment compliance, vendor systems, financial securities, Agile project management, business analysis, and SQL.</p>
 <p><b>Duration</b></p>
 <p>For current 4th year students, the internship will be throughout the school year as class schedules allow. Exceptional hires may be offered a full-time position with the company at the end of the internship.</p>
 <p><b>Eligible Applicants</b></p>
 <p>The following candidates are encouraged to apply:</p>
 <ul>
  <li>Currently enrolled 4th year students in pursuit of a Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Business, Economics, Accounting, or a related field</li>
  <li>Honorably discharged military veterans</li>
 </ul>
 <p><b>Requirements</b></p>
 <ul>
  <li>Interest in investment management, compliance, and business analysis</li>
  <li>Solid written and oral communication skills</li>
  <li>Familiarity with Microsoft Office products, especially Excel and PowerPoint</li>
  <li>Knowledge of SQL and relational databases is a plus</li>
  <li>Must be able to pass an IMP-administered logic test</li>
  <li>Must be authorized to work in the United States</li>
  <li>Must be able to work during normal business hours on a set weekly schedule</li>
  <li>Being able to commute to our Boston office is a plus</li>
  <li>Ability to work from home - Hybrid</li>
 </ul>
 <p>Salary: $30/hr<br/> Hours: Minimum of 10-15 hours per week is required<br/> <br/> Location: Boston, MA/Hybrid</p>
</div>

class="js-match-insights-provider-e6s05i eu4oa1w0"><h3 class="js-match-insights-provider-11n8e9a e1tiznh50">Job type</h3><div class="js-match-insights-provider-kyg8or eu4oa1w0"><ul class="js-match-insights-provider-h884c4 eu4oa1w0"><li class="js-match-insights-provider-hj3618 eu4oa1w0" data-testid="list-item"><div class="js-match-insights-provider-1m98ica e1xnxm2i0" data-testid="Internship-tile"><div class="js-match-insights-provider-g6kqeb ecydgvn0"><div class="js-match-insights-provider-tvvxwd ecydgvn1">Internship</div><div class="js-match-insights-provider-tvvxwd ecydgvn1"></div></div></div></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class="js-match-insights-provider-bbq8li eu4oa1w0"></div></div><div aria-orientation="horizontal" class="js-match-insights-provider-1lugej0 e15p7aqh1" role="separator"><span class="js-match-insights-provider-1b6omqv esbq1260"><span>&amp;nbsp;</span></span></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="mosaic mosaic-empty-zone" id="mosaic-aboveFullJobDescription"></div><div class="mosaic mosaic-empty-zone" id="mosaic-aboveExtractedJobDescription"></div><div class="mosaic-zone" id="mosaic-ssrVJModals"><div class="mosaic mosaic-provider-passport-intercept" id="mosaic-provider-passport-intercept"><div data-testid="passport-intercept-type-modal"></div></div></div><div id="jobDescriptionTitle"><h2 class="css-wpzt8u e1tiznh50" id="jobDescriptionTitleHeading" tabindex="-1">Full job description</h2></div><div class="jobsearch-JobComponent-description css-16y4thd eu4oa1w0" id="jobDescriptionText"><div>
 Overview: 
 <div>
  BerryDunn’s Management and IT Consulting Group (MITG) is looking for a <b>Management and IT Consulting Intern</b> to join our team for the summer 2025 approximately June - August. Our Management and IT Consulting Group has a long history of working collaboratively with clients to provide independent and objective consulting services that address challenges associated with organization, management, and information technology. We help our clients create, grow, and protect value through evaluating their use of information systems, streamlining processes, developing management skills, and planning for future technology acquisitions, infrastructure, and resource needs.
 </div>
 <div></div>
 <div>
  <br/> You will be immersed in dynamic, in-person learning and get to connect with other interns and experience the company culture firsthand. This 10-week summer internship is based at either our Portland, ME headquarters, our Waltham, MA or Phoenix, AZ office.
 </div>
 <div></div>
 <div>
  <b><br/> We have </b><b>internship</b><b> openings </b><b>with our Management &amp; Information Technology group for:</b>
 </div>
 <ul>
  <li>Summer session running from June 3, 2025, through August 8, 2025.</li>
 </ul>
 <div>
  Please provide the following in your application:
 </div>
 <ul>
  <li><b> Resume</b></li>
  <li><b> Unofficial transcript</b></li>
 </ul> You Will: 
 <div>
  As an intern with our group, you will work on a variety of engagements within our core practice areas: healthcare, higher education, IT governance, risk and compliance, commercial, and workforce/well being. We do not expect our interns to have previous experience working in these industries, however, MITG interns should be eager to learn quickly as you work across teams and consulting projects.
 </div>
 <div></div>
 <div>
  <br/> You will work alongside our team serving our clients, participate in business development activities, perform research and analysis, and contribute to other value-added tasks for the group.
 </div>
 <div></div>
 <div>
  <br/> Your summer internship will fly by as you work on relevant, meaningful engagements, directly contribute to ongoing projects, and learn how to be an effective consultant across different types of clients.
 </div>
 <div></div>
 <div>
  <br/> All new team members are partnered with an experienced BerryDunn team member as an advisor to help guide you through your internship. The rest of your team will assign work, answer questions, meet regularly with you and provide constructive feedback as you hone your skills toward becoming a full-time consultant.
 </div>
 <div></div>
 <div>
  <br/> An internship with MITG will challenge you, build your communication skills, give you exposure to a variety of client engagements, require you to develop solutions to complex problems, enhance your ability to work on a team, and allow you to gain hands-on consulting experience.
 </div>
 <div></div>
 <div>
  <br/> We consider our interns as we would our full-time hires and have a long history of hiring interns as full-time staff consultants after they complete the internship program.
 </div><br/>
 <div></div> You Have: 
 <ul>
  <li>Currently enrolled in a BS/BA/MS Degree in one of these areas: business, economics, risk management, information systems audit and control, information technology management, strategic management, management information systems, health science or computer science.</li>
  <li>Must be legally authorized to work in the United States without the need for employer sponsorship, now or at any time in the future.</li>
  <li>History of high performance in academics and previous roles.</li>
  <li>Interest in pursuing a career in consulting</li>
  <li>Track record of team project and leadership experience.</li>
  <li>Relevant work experience in one of the fields above is a plus.</li>
  <li>Drive and initiative to learn.</li>
  <li>Demonstrated experience in relationship building and teamwork.</li>
  <li>Excellent writing and communication skills.</li>
  <li>Strong computer skills including MS Office, Word, Excel and PowerPoint.</li>
 </ul> Compensation Details: 
 <div>
  <i> The hourly rate for this role is $28 per hour. This rate represents BerryDunn’s good faith and reasonable estimate of the possible compensation at the time of posting. If an applicant possesses experience, education, or other qualifications in excess of the minimum requirements for this posting, that applicant is encouraged to apply, and a final rate may then be based on those additional qualifications; compensation decisions are dependent on the facts and circumstances of each case. The rate of the finalist selected for this role will be based on a variety of factors, including but not limited to, years of experience, depth of experience, seniority, merit, education, training, amount of travel, and other relevant business considerations.</i>
 </div> BerryDunn Benefits &amp; Culture: 
 <p>Our people are what make BerryDunn special, and in return we strive to support our employees and help them thrive. Eligible employees have access to benefits that go beyond what’s expected to support their physical, mental, career, social, and financial well-being. Visit our website for a complete list of benefits and a look into our culture: Experience BerryDunn.</p>
 <p></p>
 <p><b><br/> About BerryDunn</b></p>
 <div>
  BerryDunn is a leading national professional services firm providing assurance, tax, and consulting services to businesses, nonprofits, and government agencies throughout the US and its territories. Since 1974, we have been a client-centered, people-first firm with a mission to empower the meaningful growth of our people, clients, and communities. Led by CEO Sarah Belliveau, the firm has been recognized for its efforts in creating a diverse and inclusive workplace culture, and for its focus on learning, development, and well-being. Learn more at berrydunn.com.
 </div>
 <div></div>
 <div>
  <i><br/> We will ensure that individuals are provided reasonable accommodation to participate in the job application or interview process or perform essential job functions. Please contact </i><i>careers@berrydunn.com</i><i> to request an accommodation.</i>
 </div>
 <div></div>
 <div>
  <i><br/> We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender, gender identity or expression, or veteran status. We are proud to be an equal opportunity workplace.</i>
 </div>
 <div></div>
 <div>
  <i><br/> #BD_CT</i>

Our Management and IT Consulting Group has a long history of working collaboratively with clients to provide independent and objective consulting services that address challenges associated with organization, management, and information technology. We help our clients create, grow, and protect value through evaluating their use of information systems, streamlining processes, developing management skills, and planning for future technology acquisitions, infrastructure, and resource needs.\n\nYou will be immersed in dynamic, in-person learning and get to connect with other interns and experience the company culture firsthand. This 10-week summer internship is based at either our Portland, ME headquarters, our Waltham, MA or Phoenix, AZ office.\n\nWe have internship openings with our Management & Information Technology group for:\n\nSummer session running from June 3, 2025, through August 8, 2025.\n\nPlease provide the following in your application:\n\nResume\nUnofficial transcript\nYou Will:\n\nAs an intern with our group, you will work on a variety of engagements within our core practice areas: healthcare, higher education, IT governance, risk and compliance, commercial, and workforce\u002Fwell being. We do not expect our interns to have previous experience working in these industries, however, MITG interns should be eager to learn quickly as you work across teams and consulting projects.\n\nYou will work alongside our team serving our clients, participate in business development activities, perform research and analysis, and contribute to other value-added tasks for the group.\n\nYour summer internship will fly by as you work on relevant, meaningful engagements, directly contribute to ongoing projects, and learn how to be an effective consultant across different types of clients.\n\nAll new team members are partnered with an experienced BerryDunn team member as an advisor to help guide you through your internship. The rest of your team will assign work, answer questions, meet regularly with you and provide constructive feedback as you hone your skills toward becoming a full-time consultant.\n\nAn internship with MITG will challenge you, build your communication skills, give you exposure to a variety of client engagements, require you to develop solutions to complex problems, enhance your ability to work on a team, and allow you to gain hands-on consulting experience.\n\nWe consider our interns as we would our full-time hires and have a long history of hiring interns as full-time staff consultants after they complete the internship program.\n\nYou Have:\nCurrently enrolled in a BS\u002FBA\u002FMS Degree in one of these areas: business, economics, risk management, information systems audit and control, information technology management, strategic management, management information systems, health science or computer science.\nMust be legally authorized to work in the United States without the need for employer sponsorship, now or at any time in the future.\nHistory of high performance in academics and previous roles.\nInterest in pursuing a career in consulting\nTrack record of team project and leadership experience.\nRelevant work experience in one of the fields above is a plus.\nDrive and initiative to learn.\nDemonstrated experience in relationship building and teamwork.\nExcellent writing and communication skills.\nStrong computer skills including MS Office, Word, Excel and PowerPoint.\nCompensation Details:\n\nThe hourly rate for this role is $28 per hour. This rate represents BerryDunn’s good faith and reasonable estimate of the possible compensation at the time of posting. If an applicant possesses experience, education, or other qualifications in excess of the minimum requirements for this posting, that applicant is encouraged to apply, and a final rate may then be based on those additional qualifications; compensation decisions are dependent on the facts and circumstances of each case. The rate of the finalist selected for this role will be based on a variety of factors, including but not limited to, years of experience, depth of experience, seniority, merit, education, training, amount of travel, and other relevant business considerations.\n\nBerryDunn Benefits & Culture:\n\nOur people are what make BerryDunn special, and in return we strive to support our employees and help them thrive. Eligible employees have access to benefits that go beyond what’s expected to support their physical, mental, career, social, and financial well-being.
